.TH man 1 "05 October 2015" "1.0" "location man page"
.SH NAME
location \- search information about a geographical place
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B location
[\fB\-e\fR]
[\fB\-s\fR \fIseparator\fR]
.I location
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B location
queries the Yahoo! database for information about a geographical place.
It displays the name of the location, the state, the country, the latitude,
the longitude and the WOEID. The search can have multiple results.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-e
Output in a format suitable for parsing line by line.
Otherwise a more human readable form is used.
.TP
.BI "\-s " separator
Specifies the field separator if the
.B \-e
option is used. The default is "|".
.SH EXAMPLES
To search for a location named "Springfield" use
.PP
.nf
.RS
location "Springfield"
.RE
.fi
.PP
.SH SEE ALSO
weather(1)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
Wilfried Meindl <wilfried.meindl@gmail.com>

